title: For Sale:  VERY Collectible - S&W Model 3000 - NEVER FIRED
postcontent:
As NEW - Never been fired!!! (Over 25 years old.)

The first with CASH only will own this shotgun & you pick up.

The pump-action Model 3000 was imported by Smith & Wesson in the early '80s to compete with the popular Remington 870. It's "split lifter" feeding mechanism addressed the Model 870s biggest drawback, the possibility of a "jam" if the operator "short-stroked" the action while racking a fresh shell into the chamber.

The Models 3000, along with the semi-auto Models 1000 and the centerfire Model 1500 line of rifles, were discontinued in 1984 when S&W's corporate parent Lear Siegler was acquired by Bangor Punta. 

These Model 3000 shotguns were well made, durable and very robust.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom AR15 Package
postcontent:
This is a custom AR15, built by me, a gunsmithing student at MCC with the help of a practicing gunsmith.

The lower is a Del-Ton brand receiver with a DPMS LPK.  The stock is an ACE ARFX buttstock and contains a standard A2 buffer with a CS spring.  The pistol grip is a Hogue.

The upper is an RGUNS (Cerro Forge) brand flattop receiver with a properly torqued and accurized 5.56mm barrel, so it will shoot both 5.56mm as well as .223.  Both the barrel and the receiver have M4 feed ramps.  The FSB has been replaced with a low profile gas block, which is concealed beneath the handguard.  The handguard is a Troy/VTAC Alpha 9” modular rail handguard.  All screws/rails/rail backers/installation wrenches are included.  A MaTech rear BUIS adjustable for windage and elevation out to 600 meters and a flip-up front sight are installed.

Included in the package are three black Magpul 30 round PMAGS, over 100 rounds of ammunition (76 rounds of PMC Bronze 55gr .223/49 rounds of 62gr Green Tip 5.56mm XM855, a Plano hard case, OD single point sling, and laser with remote switch.  The laser is not currently installed, but I would be happy to install it to POA at your chosen distance.  The adjustment screwdriver is included as well.

Test firing is fine with cash in hand, as long as you have somewhere to do it.  If you have any questions, feel free to ask.

I'm fairly firm on the price, but if I find I'm asking too much I may lower it.  I'm in no hurry to sell.  The only substantial trade I will consider is for a motorcycle, preferably a late 80s to early 90s Nighthawk at least 650cc but willing to consider others.  I may take other trades with at least $1k cash.  Will require bill of sale (a copy for each of us) and will need NCDL info.  If it matters relative to a trade, I have an NCCHP.

title: For Sale:  High Standard Sport King Special. Model A1041
location: Eastern Jackson County, Kansas City, Missouri
postcontent:
High Standard Sport King Special. Model A1041. Competition grade rifle.
I bought this rifle specifically to shoot competition. It was recommended by several of my shooting friends as being one of the most reliable and accurate rifle on the market today.
